Use Sniffer to capture IP packet.

CAT setup
=========

To capture optical link (always full duplex), need to set up SPAN session
from Cat4k:

conf t
monitor session 1 source int g1/1 rx
monitor session 1 dest int g3/13

We can have up to 12 sessions.
rx means capture input, not output.

Since the input is GE, need to forward to a 10/100/1000 port.
Otherwise will have speed mismatch and drop packets.


Sniffer
=======

Capture | Start
On the left pane, choose Objects.
Then choose DLC to monitor L2
Station to monitor L3
Connection to monitor UDP ports.

Capture | Stop and Display
Choose Decode on bottom tab to look at capture content.

A ring buffer of 256 MB will be used for capture.

The saved file will have .cap extension.
